{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:sirach.3",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 3,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 3 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:1",
      "text": "Hear me, your father, O my children, and do what you hear, that you all may be safe.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:2",
      "text": "For the Lord honors the father over the children, and has confirmed the judgment of the mother over her sons.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:3",
      "text": "He who honors his father will make atonement for sins.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:4",
      "text": "He who gives glory to his mother is as one who lays up treasure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:5",
      "text": "Whoever honors his father will have joy in his own children. He will be heard in the day of his prayer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:6",
      "text": "He who gives glory to his father will have length of days. He who listens to the Lord will bring rest to his mother,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:7",
      "text": "and will serve under his parents, as to masters.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:8",
      "text": "Honor your father in deed and word, that a blessing may come upon you from him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:9",
      "text": "For the blessing of the father establishes the houses of children, but the curse of the mother roots out the foundations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:10",
      "text": "Don’t glorify yourself in the dishonor of your father, for your father’s dishonor is no glory to you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:11",
      "text": "For the glory of a man is from the honor of his father, and a mother in dishonor is a reproach to her children.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:12",
      "text": "My son, help your father in his old age, and don’t grieve him as long as he lives.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:13",
      "text": "If he fails in understanding, have patience with him. Don’t dishonor him in your full strength.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:14",
      "text": "For the kindness to your father will not be forgotten. Instead of sins it will be added to build you up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:15",
      "text": "In the day of your affliction it will be remembered for you, as fair weather upon ice, so your sins will also melt away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:16",
      "text": "He who forsakes his father is as a blasphemer. He who provokes his mother is cursed by the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:17",
      "text": "My son, go on with your business in humility; so you will be loved by an acceptable man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:18",
      "text": "The greater you are, humble yourself the more, and you will find favor before the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:20",
      "text": "For the power of the Lord is great, and he is glorified by those who are lowly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:21",
      "text": "Don’t seek things that are too hard for you, and don’t search out things that are above your strength.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:22",
      "text": "Think about the things that have been commanded you, for you have no need of the things that are secret.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:23",
      "text": "Don’t be overly busy in tasks that are beyond you, for more things are shown to you than men can understand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:24",
      "text": "For the conceit of many has led them astray. Evil opinion has caused their judgment to slip.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:25",
      "text": "There is no light without eyes. There is no wisdom without knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:26",
      "text": "A stubborn heart will do badly at the end. He who loves danger will perish in it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:27",
      "text": "A stubborn heart will be burdened with troubles. The sinner will heap sin upon sins.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:28",
      "text": "The calamity of the proud has no healing, for a weed of wickedness has taken root in him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:29",
      "text": "The heart of the prudent will understand a proverb. A wise man desires the ear of a listener.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:30",
      "text": "Water will quench a flaming fire; almsgiving will make atonement for sins.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.3.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 3,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 3:31",
      "text": "He who repays good turns is mindful of that which comes afterward. In the time of his falling he will find a support.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
